# UI Theme/Color Change Guard

- Do not change themes, color palettes, accent colors, dark/light styling, or other visual color tokens unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Do not introduce theme/color “improvements” proactively.
- If a request is ambiguous, keep current theme/color behavior unchanged.
- Allowed only when:
  - the user directly asks for theme/color/styling changes, or
  - the requested feature clearly requires a minimal inferred color tweak.

## Examples

- `Do`: implement logic/bugfix/features without altering colors.
- `Do`: ask for clarification if a visual request could imply color changes but is not explicit.
- `Don't`: restyle components, swap classes, or adjust theme variables as part of unrelated fixes.
